Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.58,0:00:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Okay everyone, let's begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.00,0:00:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, as our presenters, we'll be having these gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.00,0:00:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Woah, so many!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Tamura Kenji, Chocolate Planet, and Kasuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,TOOS!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey that was funny, do it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.80,0:00:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,TOOOS!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.50,0:00:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.90,0:00:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's {\i1}really{\i0} funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.90,0:00:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Really funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.50,0:00:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay but did anybody even notice Kenji go {\i1}cha~{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.50,0:00:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, you didn't hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was right in the center! A center-cha.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you really cha-ed, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.00,0:00:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's get on with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.00,0:00:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay everybody, it's what you've been waiting for...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an "everybody's theory" special.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.50,0:01:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, who are we starting with?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.50,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A real star duo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the theory we've chosen this time is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.40,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're at home alone, if somebody knocks on the door while you're on the toilet, you'll end up saying "I'm in here!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.00,0:01:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, right? If you were alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you be too terrified?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.50,0:01:49.00,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You would, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but before the fear sets in...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:54.20,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You'd reply by reflex.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:01:59.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I see. So it's fear versus reflex.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.90,0:02:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.90,0:02:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well if it were a person's voice, I'd be scared, but I wonder if you could reply to a knock with a knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You might just reply with a knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.50,0:02:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It would only be really scary knowing for sure there's a person there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.50,0:02:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A theory that says: even if you're at home alone, if somebody knocks on the door while you're on the toilet, you'll say "I'm in here!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.50,0:02:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawai from Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A hidden camera has been placed in his home while he's living alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.50,0:02:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,30 minutes pass until the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.50,0:03:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,While Kawai enters the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.40,0:03:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A staff member hiding on his balcony comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Woah, that startled me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.50,0:03:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He locked it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't say "I'm here."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he didn't seem to be coming out, let's try it once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Woah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.60,0:03:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.80,0:03:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Wednesday Downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.10,0:03:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do shit like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Die. Die, die, die, for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.90,0:03:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I really can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the line between right and wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, they didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.90,0:04:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, he didn't say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear won.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.20,0:04:12.00,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Of course it would!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He locked the door so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.30,0:04:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be so scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the next theory we've chosen for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how unpalatable the food, if you were on a streak catching marshmallows in your mouth, you'd eat it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The targets this time were called in under the pretenses of a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nadaru, from Colocolo Chittychitty Peppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've done it live once before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't remember at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.40,0:04:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit similing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The unpalatable thing Nishino will be throwing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.00,0:05:08.00,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Hornet larvae
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, he's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think he'd be this good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nadaru smoothly catches a number of marshmallows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.60,0:05:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He keeps sticking his hand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.60,0:05:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks like Itsugi Hiroshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.90,0:05:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he notice it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.20,0:05:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He ate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:47.80,Red - right,,0,0,0,,Larva
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:49.30,Blue - right,,0,0,0,,Marshmallow
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:51.30,Red - right,,0,0,0,,Larva
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.00,0:05:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:06:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He feels something is off, but he continues...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In total, three larvae entered his mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, to reveal the prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.30,0:06:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You put some wet thing in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.00,0:06:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I saw something funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.50,0:06:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice anything unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there was some kind of wet marshmallow
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.40,0:06:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the wet marshmallow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.20,0:06:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell did you do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.90,0:06:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some wet marshmallow...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.70,0:06:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.30,0:06:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory is that if you're catching marshmallows, you'd eat whatever nasty stuff that gets thrown in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.40,0:07:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was larvae??
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Stag beetle larvae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not stag beetle. Hornet larvae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was only hornet larvae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.30,0:07:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's your reaction?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.80,0:07:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're relieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As a kid I used to be fed hornet larvae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By who?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.40,0:07:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I always said that I didn't want to eat it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.40,0:07:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least it's not from a stag beetle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Chocolate Planet's selection from everybody's theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving on, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the names of elementary schools and middle schools, the word "east" is particularly common
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a look at the kanto region, and count up schools with "north," "south," "east," and "west" in their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.00,0:07:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting at the fourth most frequent, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.40,0:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,North, at 163 schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.40,0:08:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In third place...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.90,0:08:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,West, at 213 schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.40,0:08:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In second place...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,South, at 247 schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.40,0:08:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, "east" was indeed the most frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, according to our researchers, the reasoning for this was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.40,0:08:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,East was most common.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're sitting in a sauna, you should be able to eat scalding foods with no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:34.10,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Cause you'd already feel hot all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.10,0:08:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For our challengers this time, we have this pair, regulars of the show by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're both mostly able to handle the temperature of the food under normal conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who enters the sauna is decided by rock-paper-scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.40,0:08:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Abarareru-kun's sauna is set to 99ºC.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikezaki's room, right outside, is 25ºC.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Two pieces left!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.20,0:09:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can do it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Ikezaki's already down to his last egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.50,0:09:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm done! I'm done!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.80,0:09:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.80,0:09:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The air in here is unreal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.80,0:09:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Being inside the sauna...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:09:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was the food any less hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:10:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, of course it was hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.80,0:10:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The next theory from Chocolate Planet is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put your pants on while the hem is sewn shut, you'll fall down
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:14.80,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just outside our last location, we find Ikezaki again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:36.80,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Right, that's what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The last theory chosen by Chocolate Planet today is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.80,0:10:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kids who complete a bike tour across Japan during their summer vacation would grow up to be splendid adults
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.20,0:10:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This time our subjects are brothers who completed a bike tour of Japan in the summer of 1997.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.90,0:11:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers started in Ashiya, Hyogo prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.00,0:11:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In 44 days, they completed a tour of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In total, they biked approximately 3,300 kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They raised money for the Great Hanshin earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.30,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Participating in activities across the country, they helped with recovery from the earthquake...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.40,0:11:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In total, they raised nearly three million yen in contributions from Hyogo prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.50,0:11:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, they would go on to be splendid people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The phrasing here is scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.50,0:11:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they gonna turn out OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.70,0:11:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.00,0:11:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the older brother, Masamichi, who's now 34 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At present, what is it that you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, I do work related to the Guinness World Records.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.50,0:12:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He works for the Guinness World Records in Japan, spending his days alongside people who challenge the human limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what about the younger brother, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.10,0:12:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be the bad one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'd really like to do is support the people who endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a job that I can do to give back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say it's my calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is it that your brother is doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently my brother's living in America...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.50,0:12:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's working for Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.30,0:12:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion: they really became splendid adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.00,0:12:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Fujimon, what did you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How about that theory about schools with "east" in their name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.30,0:12:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, tell us what you thought about that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.95,0:13:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.00,0:13:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wasn't it amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There were twice as many with "east" than "north."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.50,0:13:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.00,0:13:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're messing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.80,0:13:16.70,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You seemed to be most interested in that theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.70,0:13:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but I wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.70,0:13:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Was "east" in the name of the school you attended?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.70,0:13:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well in high school it was, yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.70,0:13:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I have any reason to care about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but in the end, "east" was the most popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you make of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.00,0:13:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was clearly the most popular. By far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.70,0:13:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, going off of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.70,0:13:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're killing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.90,0:13:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.90,0:13:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Up next, everybody's theories, as chosen by Kasuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.30,0:13:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here are the theories we're doing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.90,0:14:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A theory that states the oldest property available for rent must be from the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.30,0:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well there's a lot of old buildings, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I happen to have lived in one for twenty years myself, "Mutsumi-sou."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.40,0:14:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The building was made in 1966. A 55-year old building from the Showa era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.40,0:14:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we hit the maximum age, it could be from the Edo period, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.90,0:14:29.90,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,But you don't mean a sort of cultural building...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean a place you can actually live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.50,0:14:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A theory that states the oldest property available for rent must be from the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.50,0:15:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we'll look at the oldest property available for rent in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.70,0:15:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A run-down part of the Bunkyo ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.50,0:15:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This property here was built...103 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1919 (Taisho year 8).
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.90,0:15:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A building that survived the Great Kanto earthquake and Tokyo firebombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It remains a property for people to rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.50,0:15:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For the curious, we'll take a look inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.50,0:15:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The inside's nice, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.90,0:15:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's been renovated several times, the space remains intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.90,0:15:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, the rent for the property is 120,000 yen.\N(approx. $1080 USD)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.04,0:16:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had been paying that for 103 years, the total would be 143,820,000 yen.\N(Approx. $1.3M USD)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked to the current renters about their experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets super cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.54,0:16:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.34,0:16:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Numbingly cold in the winter, and really hot in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The walls are super thin so we really hear the neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.84,0:16:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.00,0:16:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we'll expand our search to include the whole country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In Fukuchiyama, Kyoto, we came across an even older building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A detached house, currently seeking renters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.26,0:16:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,127 sq. meters, 6 rooms excluding dining and kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It may need some remodeling, but the rent is 50,000 yen.\N(Approx. $450 US)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:17:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with those four adjacent "Japanese-style rooms"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.06,0:17:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was built 127 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Meiji 27. (1894)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving on, we have a detatched house in Yamazoe village, Yamabe, Nara prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.06,0:17:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,, 204 sq. m, with 6 rooms excluding dining and kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The rent here is also 50,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitchen reflects the time in which it was built, with a kamado wood-burning stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In the bathroom, there's a goemon-style bath, still functional.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to reveal the age...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.76,0:17:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid we only have one method to prove it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.16,0:17:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes back 153 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The first year of the Meiji era [1872].
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With a house available dating back to Meiji year 1, finding a house from the edo period was all but confirmed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.56,0:18:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In what year do you the building was actually erected?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would've been the end of the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.96,0:18:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't be totally sure of it though...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the theory is nearly proved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.26,0:18:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we continue our investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In Kamigyo ward of Kyoto, we found an unusually old building.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.16,0:18:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The property has a narrow frontage, and a long entryway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.66,0:18:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, taxes were applied to the frontage, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it was built to be narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Edo period, there was a "frontage tax."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.06,0:19:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that this sort of long, narrow property was typical of the era.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.26,0:19:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the building's age...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.36,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been told it was built 350 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Although there aren't documents confirming it, stories dating the building have been passed along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.76,0:19:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Stories of a building from 1670...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.96,0:19:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're renting and currently seeking tenants.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.86,0:19:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the rent?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.66,0:19:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,80,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.46,0:19:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The bathrooms have been recently renovated...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.66,0:19:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can really feel the age of the place through its still-functional well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion: those interested should inquire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.86,0:19:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujimon, your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.36,0:19:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:20:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For the bathroom there, I think I would have preferred it in its original state, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd take as it was, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.56,0:20:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are all the comments you make going to be that gloomy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.76,0:20:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So strict!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Soooo strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.66,0:20:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's theories, as selected by Kasuga. Next up, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If elementary schools kids asked Jimmy Onishi, "Jimmy, are you getting any?" he'd be so surprised that he couldn't reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.86,0:20:39.86,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,Note: I'm not familiar with this gag— I'm pretty sure it's a dirty joke though...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! This is Jimmy Onishi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.86,0:20:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I'm here at the Edo Tokyo Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.36,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought out Jimmy to a fake TV shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.16,0:20:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok, all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna make arrangements to go in now, so please wait here for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.04,0:21:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Once he thinks the camera's stopped rolling...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.04,0:21:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy, are you getting any?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure ain't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.34,0:21:14.64,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Damn, he's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.64,0:21:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's theories, as selected by Kasuga. Up next...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.64,0:21:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere, there must be a pair of sisters like Maya and Meena, where the elder dances and the younger tells fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the RPG Dragon Quest IV, you encounter the Mahabala sisters, Maya and Meena.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.24,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Could there really be a pair of sisters living the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.94,0:21:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,For efficiency's sake, we'll start by approaching a fortune-teller.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.94,0:21:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anybody here matching that description at present.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.94,0:22:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid nobody comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something like that in Dragon Quest, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm acquainted with a number of fortune tellers, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.04,0:22:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anybody that fits the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.34,0:22:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But among those we asked...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.64,0:22:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself am a fortune teller, and my younger sister is a dancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.84,0:22:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but I guess that's the opposite?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.44,0:22:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We found the inverse of the Mahabala sisters, with a fortune-telling elder sister and a dancing younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.04,0:22:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been in America, belly dancing in New York...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.64,0:22:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They were spot-on with the dancing and fortune-telling, but unfortunately in the wrong order...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares if it's the wrong order?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.04,0:22:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we continued on with our search...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.84,0:22:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We came across a promising lead in Yokohama's Chinatown.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.44,0:23:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome. A pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.04,0:23:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ms. Hoshi, a fortune teller at the Four Pillars of Destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.64,0:23:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We've heard that your sister is a dancer. Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.84,0:23:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister's practiced traditional Japanese dance since she was a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.84,0:23:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The older sister is a practitioner of Japanese dance— that is to say, she's a dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, we've found the real-world incarnation of Maya and Meena.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.84,0:23:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been told before that you're just like Maya and Meena?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.84,0:23:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And who would they be?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.84,0:23:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it some kind of legendary tale?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.84,0:23:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.24,0:23:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, as chosen by Kasuga. Up next...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.84,0:23:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When talking about Yasu from Zun, for some reason you always have to include the "from"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.94,0:24:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do one more?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.44,0:24:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell yeah I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.24,0:24:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They really got some use out of this spot, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.04,0:24:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna show you some pictures of comedians, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.24,0:24:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us the name of their duo and then their own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.74,0:24:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.44,0:24:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Downtown, Hamada Masatoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.94,0:24:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Audrey, Kasuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.24,0:24:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Panther, Ogata.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.34,0:24:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Viking, Kotoge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.44,0:24:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Saraba Seishun no Hikari, Morita.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.44,0:24:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Zun's...Yasu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.94,0:24:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, as chosen by Kasuga. Up next...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.94,0:24:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,  It can't be possible to lap up water faster than a dog
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.94,0:24:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What, you mean like licking it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.94,0:24:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty good at licking though.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.04,0:24:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have Kuro-chan, a man confident in his tongue capabilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, if you lose, you'll get a few electric shocks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.44,0:24:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.44,0:25:16.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Looks like the dog's thirsty too
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.64,0:25:22.44,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Quit moaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.04,0:25:29.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He got it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.04,0:25:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.44,0:25:35.14,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He's going "woof."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.54,0:25:38.14,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's woofing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.04,0:25:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.04,0:25:44.54,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,It's really not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.54,0:25:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, as selected by Kasuga. Lastly, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.54,0:26:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety shoes really are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.54,0:26:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to test the theory out...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.94,0:26:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow, ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.44,0:26:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After his competition, we brought him out again as a subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.04,0:26:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The theory you'll be testing this time is "safety shoes really are safe."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.84,0:26:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety shoes are safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.24,0:26:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be using steel-toe boots, standard-issue safety shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.94,0:26:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason I've always thought safety shoes were cool, so I've worn them before, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.14,0:26:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean you wore them in private?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.94,0:26:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.64,0:26:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at those nips.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.54,0:26:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're pretty hard, huh
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.04,0:26:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The experienced Kuro-chan prepares for action...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.04,0:26:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,First...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.04,0:26:50.04,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,LEVEL ONE: BOWLING BALL
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.04,0:26:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey wait, this is pretty heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.34,0:26:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna take that and drop it on your boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.74,0:26:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,By myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.04,0:26:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.24,0:26:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really gonna be OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.04,0:26:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, this is only level one, so try to hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.94,0:27:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, how many times am I doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.04,0:27:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an everybody's theories special, so it keeps a quick pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.04,0:27:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so it's a quickie.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.44,0:27:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't hurt at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.24,0:27:22.94,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Then why'd he cry out?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.94,0:27:27.94,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,LEVEL TWO: HAMMER
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.94,0:27:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you put your foot on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.04,0:27:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually felt that one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.34,0:27:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that bowling ball earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.34,0:27:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.34,0:27:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.04,0:27:44.04,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.44,0:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do the next one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.04,0:27:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.04,0:27:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up, hold up!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.04,0:27:53.04,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,LEVEL THREE: CAR
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.54,0:27:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was gonna be run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.04,0:27:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So next...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.04,0:27:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't "yeah" me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.04,0:27:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The car's gonna run over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.64,0:28:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna run over them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.04,0:28:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.04,0:28:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I gonna be OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.24,0:28:20.24,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Is he OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.24,0:28:22.24,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Is he or isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.44,0:28:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.04,0:28:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It ran over you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It ran over me...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.04,0:28:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.74,0:28:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, I tricked you!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.04,0:28:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Trickuro-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.24,0:28:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Trickuro-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.24,0:28:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He really said Trickuro-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.04,0:28:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving on...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.44,0:28:56.44,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,LEVEL FOUR: TRUCK
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.74,0:28:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is level four.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.94,0:28:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.04,0:28:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.04,0:29:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, really, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.04,0:29:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.04,0:29:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already reached the max for what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.04,0:29:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really mean you can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.04,0:29:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, for TV reasons? Or you really just can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.04,0:29:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.54,0:29:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but like, Kuro-chan, you really really can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.84,0:29:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.64,0:29:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll end the human experimentation here for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.44,0:29:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll continue with a raw egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.74,0:29:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess they'll put it inside the boot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.44,0:29:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they put it inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.44,0:29:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.44,0:29:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You shoulda brought this out sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.44,0:29:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That was scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.04,0:29:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had this before you should've brought it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.04,0:29:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This might be even scarier than last time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.54,0:30:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The result?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.24,0:30:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.94,0:30:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.94,0:30:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's super broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.84,0:30:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.34,0:30:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole theory's scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.44,0:30:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion: there are limits to the safety of safety shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.34,0:30:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.84,0:30:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we almost ended off on the wrong foot there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.84,0:30:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean he was only considering it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.84,0:30:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If he actually went for it, we'd be finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.64,0:30:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was his animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.54,0:30:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Up next: everybody's theories, selected by Tamuken.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.54,0:30:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay everyone, I'll be the last to present today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.94,0:30:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To start off, please take a look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.94,0:31:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm hearing some surprise, but you know who this is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.94,0:31:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Bit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.94,0:31:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The impersonator?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.44,0:31:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.94,0:31:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we've brought you a theory regarding this Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.94,0:31:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.34,0:31:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If shown a caricature of Bit Takeshi and asked who it is, not a single person would reply "Bit Takeshi"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.54,0:31:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.24,0:31:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody would know who Bit Takeshi is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.24,0:31:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even among comedians, that would be tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.34,0:31:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If shown a caricature of Bit Takeshi and asked who it is, not a single person would reply "Bit Takeshi"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.04,0:31:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The entertainment industry's hit rock bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.74,0:31:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Booby-traps battle royale!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.94,0:32:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bit Takeshi's been playing Beat Takeshi alone for 42 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.84,0:32:02.34,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,I guess there is a resemblance, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.34,0:32:05.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He looks more like the old Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.94,0:32:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, we present what must be the world's first caricature of Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.24,0:32:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we take a look at it compared to a caricature of Beat Takeshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.04,0:32:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, if you look closely, you can see the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.98,0:32:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Will anybody be able to correctly name the caricature?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.94,0:32:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to show you some caricatures, so please identify them for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.94,0:32:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.94,0:32:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.44,0:32:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.84,0:32:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would Bit belong in the same group?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.94,0:32:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With those three back to back, of course they'd say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.34,0:32:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They may have been suggesting "Beat" a little too much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.34,0:32:48.34,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,They were.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.34,0:32:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, nobody said that it was Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.04,0:32:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.34,0:32:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.04,0:32:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.44,0:33:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.44,0:33:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected, it's nothing but "Beat Takeshi."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.44,0:33:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it can be done correctly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.04,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've got the big three all lined up and expect us to guess that it's "Bit Takeshi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's playing dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.04,0:33:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes a good point...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.84,0:33:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try testing if people can guess it based on Bit's picture alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.54,0:33:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.74,0:33:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi Kitano.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.34,0:33:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.04,0:33:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.        Beat-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.84,0:33:39.44,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Beat-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.44,0:33:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, out of a hundred people, zero answered "Bit Takeshi."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.64,0:33:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's possible that for lay people, Bit is simply not familiar enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.44,0:33:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we conducted an additional investigation among comedians familiar with Bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.84,0:34:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.04,0:34:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who's worked closely with Bit over the years, Haraguchi Akimasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.84,0:34:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We called him in to a fake business meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.54,0:34:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind if we asked a few questions for a survey on caricatures?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.64,0:34:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The result...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.74,0:34:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.24,0:34:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.84,0:34:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.04,0:34:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi who?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.94,0:34:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.74,0:34:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.04,0:34:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.34,0:34:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The correct answer was Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.54,0:34:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, he didn't answer "Bit" either.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.04,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Incidentially, here's one of Beat Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.94,0:34:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohhh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.94,0:34:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, yeah...that was pretty rude of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.50,0:34:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.64,0:34:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel kinda embarassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.58,0:35:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Up next is a longtime friend of Bit and a regular of the Kisara*, Vermont Hideki.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.58,0:35:01.98,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,* Sokkuri Kan-kisara is an event held at a pub full of lookalike entertainers. Vermont Hideki was originally imitating Hideki Saijo (see his Vermont Curry commerical)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideki's really not looking the part.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.78,0:35:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.18,0:35:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you bring it closer? My eyesight's really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.98,0:35:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sanma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.18,0:35:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.48,0:35:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.98,0:35:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi who?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.58,0:35:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.98,0:35:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is a friend of both Bit and Beat, Matsumura Fumihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.48,0:35:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Akashiya Sanma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.28,0:35:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.98,0:35:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitano Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.38,0:35:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.38,0:35:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.08,0:35:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.78,0:35:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.08,0:35:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, he too was unable to reach the answer straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.38,0:35:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...there's something about him that looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.68,0:35:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,too poor to be Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.33,0:35:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Up next, a junior to Bit before making it big...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.99,0:36:01.99,Hamada Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Oh really!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.99,0:36:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Audrey's Kasuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.98,0:36:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.48,0:36:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.72,0:36:07.98,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He'll know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.38,0:36:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.58,0:36:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi who?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.58,0:36:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Beat Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.68,0:36:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your final answer, once more, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.68,0:36:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.08,0:36:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.78,0:36:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.48,0:36:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Kitano Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.18,0:36:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.28,0:36:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? But that's Takeshi-san, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.88,0:36:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The correct answer was Bit Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.28,0:36:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.58,0:36:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be Bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.78,0:36:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi Kitano...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.98,0:36:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.88,0:36:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, yeah. When you line them up like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.48,0:36:39.58,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,You say "actually" like it was obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.38,0:36:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.88,0:36:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Among comedians who know Bit well, zero were able to identify him straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.78,0:36:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For our final subject, we'll test Bit himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.48,0:36:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If he can't get it right either, our theory is as good as proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.98,0:37:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, y'know...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.38,0:37:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanma-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.78,0:37:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Makin' it easy, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.48,0:37:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.48,0:37:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.08,0:37:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.48,0:37:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Or who I'm impersonating, I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.58,0:37:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's who I'm impersonating, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.98,0:37:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.58,0:37:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your final answer once again, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.18,0:37:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.18,0:37:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.88,0:37:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.88,0:37:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.48,0:37:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion: Bit Takeshi is the first to achieve total victory in a "zero people" theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.08,0:37:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.08,0:37:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.08,0:37:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we've been doing these "zero people" theories all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.78,0:37:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a first?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.48,0:37:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, thanks to Bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.68,0:37:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't a very close match.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.68,0:37:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We kinda knew what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.68,0:37:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way it was done wasn't that fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.68,0:37:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In that order, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.68,0:37:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The big three.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.68,0:37:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, so that's Bit's fault, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.98,0:37:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.18,0:38:02.08,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You're really not that funny today, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.08,0:38:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, as selected by Tamuken. Up next, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.08,0:38:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've been locked in a room, after checking the lock once, you wouldn't notice if it were unlocked afterwords
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.38,0:38:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The set up is as follows...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.88,0:38:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A victim has been locked in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.48,0:38:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please remove your eye mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.38,0:38:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mantenro's Ootoni.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.38,0:38:49.38,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He kinda got big, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.08,0:38:53.08,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,What's up with the coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.88,0:38:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.88,0:38:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.58,0:39:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not thinking he has to do anything in particular, ten minutes pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.38,0:39:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.28,0:39:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He realizes that he's been locked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.28,0:39:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,'scuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.88,0:39:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,'scuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.08,0:39:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,15 minutes after being in the room, the door is quietly unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.48,0:39:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,'scuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.08,0:39:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,'scuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.38,0:39:41.98,Matsumoto Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.48,0:39:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anybody there?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.18,0:39:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.98,0:39:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, he did not notice the door being suddenly unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.98,0:40:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like that, four hours pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.88,0:40:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.98,0:40:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really not allowed to leave at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.48,0:40:12.18,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,He really has no idea what this is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.92,0:40:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.48,0:40:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, what is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.68,0:40:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He notices.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.08,0:40:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it okay if I leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.28,0:40:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.70,0:40:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.28,0:40:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.88,0:40:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.78,0:40:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, selected by Tamuken.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.68,0:41:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Up next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.68,0:40:59.28,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,Four hours, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.78,0:41:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At the sushi restaurant in Japan furthest from the ocean, the freshness should be a concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.98,0:41:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's locate the sushi restaurant furthest from the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.08,0:41:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,According to geographical research, the furthest location is at this point in Saku, Nagano.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.08,0:41:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this part of Saku, there are approximately 20 sushi restaurants.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.58,0:41:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, the closest restaurant we found was...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.98,0:41:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,this 57-year old establishment, Miyako Sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.08,0:41:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It would seem that this is the furthest sushi restaurant in Japan from the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.38,0:41:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.28,0:41:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving along, to get to the point...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to be rude, but is the freshness a concern?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.38,0:42:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.28,0:42:00.98,Default Talking Over,,0,0,0,,That {\i1}is{\i0} rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.98,0:42:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,From both Toyosu and Niigata...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.28,0:42:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we get fish coming in every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.98,0:42:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we're right in the middle, we actually have supply from both directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.98,0:42:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, the freshness wasn't a concern at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.98,0:42:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's theories, selected by Tamuken. Up next...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.48,0:42:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If a child wearing Hotei-print clothes were to get lost at a shopping mall, he could be found by intercom with the message "calling for the child wearing Hotei-print clothes..."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.28,0:42:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, our theory will be tested by a three-year old kitted out in Hotei-print.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.48,0:42:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have him play a lost child in the shopping mall here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.28,0:42:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.38,0:42:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a lost child here...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.28,0:42:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What sort of announcement will be made?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.48,0:43:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, the supervisor is called in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.28,0:43:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how the announcement is made by a staff member who isn't aware of our theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.88,0:43:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The result...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.48,0:42:45.48,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,** The Hotei-print ({\i1}hoteigara{\i0}) is the signature design of rock musician Hotei Tomoyasu.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.28,0:43:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling all customers...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.18,0:43:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, at our entrance, a lost child was reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.38,0:43:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The child is a boy about five years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.58,0:43:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,wearing black and white leopard-print jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.68,0:43:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Would the customer responsible for this child...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.18,0:43:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,please make their way to the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.98,0:43:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's theories, as selected by Tamuken. Lastly...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.48,0:43:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When talking about Yasu from Zun, for some reason you always have to include the "from"\N ~Part Two~
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.78,0:43:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Downtown, Hamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.88,0:43:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Audrey...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.48,0:43:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Kasuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.18,0:44:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Cocorico...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.48,0:44:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Kondo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.58,0:44:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Zenko-Ji...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.58,0:44:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Baldy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.68,0:44:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Salaryman...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.08,0:44:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoten...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:25.48,Red - above - small,,0,0,0,,* Shoten - classic rakugo TV program
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.48,0:44:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.98,0:44:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.08,0:44:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, Jimmy hardly knows the names of any comedians at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.58,0:44:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinda pisses you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.08,0:44:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we need a new referee.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.78,0:44:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujimon, going back to that place far from the water...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.08,0:44:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you make of the freshness proposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.98,0:44:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.98,0:44:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole country's pretty connected...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.28,0:44:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has been for a while, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.38,0:44:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.28,0:45:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's being delivered, it's gonna come pretty quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.00,0:45:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, but y'know, actually, there was delivery from both parts of the country, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.28,0:45:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you make of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.78,0:45:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah but actually it was delivery on—
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.78,0:45:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,both of the–
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.78,0:45:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,killl meeeeee.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.68,0:45:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme a damn break.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.18,0:45:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But if they've been around for 57 years already, it must've been pretty tough in the old days...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.08,0:45:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true. 57 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.28,0:45:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.28,0:45:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,, news to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.78,0:45:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, even Kanda-san noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.48,0:45:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it together, man.

